display_date: made late 17th century; engraved late 19th century
title: Cup and cover
description: Cylindrical cup on three ball feet. Lower part, repousse shells and leaves; upper two thirds engraved with strapwork and scrolls with masks of crowned woman, turbaned, bearded man and faun. Three engraved ovals, with woman standing amidst waves (Aphrodite), a fairy-like winged woman, faun with thunderbolt.  Domed cover with repousse band of shells and leaves, and ball knob.
name: Cup and cover
